    <briefdescription>
<para>Segment Automata including structs and algorithms. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>These are automata whose state space can be split into several segments connected by ε-transitions in a chain. No other ε-transitions are allowed. As a consequence, no ε-transitions can appear in a cycle. Segment automaton can have initial states only in the first segment and final states only in the last segment. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
